    "Annotations": [],
    "name": "SafetyConfirmationInboundFlow",
    "description": "Safety Confirmation inbound voice flow (Phase 9.1). Sets Polly ja-JP/Mizuki voice, invokes InboundHandler Lambda with step=identify to classify the caller (E.164 lookup against Employee_Master.PhoneNumberIndex GSI + nearest active Cycle selection), then branches on the returned 'flow' Contact Attribute into one of four paths: ACTIVE_CYCLE (record + InboundGuidanceText TTS + 30s Wait + InboundHandler step=finalize + Disconnect), NO_CYCLE / NOT_REGISTERED / CYCLE_TERMINATED (guidance playback + Disconnect, no recording, no Response update). Substitution placeholders: ${InboundHandlerFnArn}, ${InboundGuidanceText}. DTMF is intentionally absent per Requirement 5.6. Inbound_Contact record write, Cycle-tied Response update (callResultCodes += INBOUND), and TranscribeStarter chaining are owned by the InboundHandler Lambda (Phase 9.2), not by this flow.",
    "type": "contactFlow",
    "status": "PUBLISHED",
    "hash": {}
  },
